Prep. Committee Formed in Pakistan 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 1 (KCNA) -- An inaugural ceremony of the Pakistan Preparatory Committee for Commemorating the Day of the Sun and February 16, birthday of leader Kim Jong Il was held in Islamabad on January 20.
 At the ceremony the chairman of the Pakistan-Korea Friendship Association made public the preparatory committee consisting of a secretary and 8 members with Organizing Secretary of the Pakistan Islamic Federation Achim Choudri as its chairman. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the preparatory committee in a speech made a proposal to hold diverse significant friendly and cultural functions to strengthen the ties with the Korean people and deepen friendship  on the occasion of the holiday of February and continue this work till the Day of the Sun, birthday of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A letter to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the ceremony.

Walking March from U.S. Embassy to Building of GNP Declared in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 1 (KCNA) -- The South Headquarters of the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification reportedly called a press conference in front of the U.S. embassy in Seoul on Jan. 28 to declare a walking march from the embassy to the building of the south Korean "Grand National Party" (GNP) and said that it would start a vigorous anti-U.S. and anti-GNP campaign this year.
 Noting that the main obstacles in the way of our nation's advance are the United States and the GNP, the participants in the press conference stated that they decided to make a walking march from the U.S. embassy to the buildings of the GNP and the "National Assembly" everyday till February 7 to disclose and denounce the nature of the U.S. and the GNP. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A written declaration of the march was issued at the press conference. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The declaration referred to the fact that the U.S. has imposed political, economic and military pressure and sanctions against the north and is now resorting to such undisguised moves against the north as deploying up-to-date military hardware in and around the Korean peninsula and launching military drills. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The declaration said that the GNP is making desperate efforts to cover up its irregularities and corruption with the approach of the "general election" and that if the moves of the U.S. and the GNP are left intact it would result in serious consequences. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After the press conference the participants made a walking march, distributing propaganda literature among citizens and conducting a signature campaign.

Rodong Sinmun on Japan's Overseas Military Operations 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 1 (KCNA) -- Japan recently dispatched large armed forces of its "Self-Defence Forces" to Iraq, a battle field between the occupation army and the resisting forces. This is a practical measure of the first stage for overseas military operations of the Japanese militarists.
 Rodong Sinmun says this in a signed commentary today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The news analyst continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The wind of militarization is blowing stronger in Japan from the beginning of the New Year and the moves to institute a war-oriented constitution and the dispatch of SDF armed forces to the battle field for aggressive overseas military operations have become undisguised. This is the first grave development ever since the defeat of the Japanese imperialists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 And this is a prelude to the overseas aggression of the Japanese militarists which may bring immeasurable misfortune and disasters to humankind again in the 21st century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The revival of Japanese militarism and overseas expansion moves are evoking great alertness in the surrounding countries and at home and abroad. As the desire and demand for independence and peace are the main trend of the present times, Japan should understand that no one will pardon those enemies going against the trend. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the Japanese reactionary ruling quarters, oblivious of this and overheated by the revival of militarism and overseas expansion moves, recklessly run amuck, they would follow in the wake of Tojyo clan, special-class war criminals who were ostracized by history, for launching the war of aggression to realize a foolish dream of the "Greater East Asia Co-prosperity Sphere" in the past.

Japan's Adoption of Anti-DPRK Law Assailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 1 (KCNA) -- Japan passed amendment to the law on foreign exchange and trade with foreign countries through the House of Representatives on Jan. 28 in a bid to support by law its moves to strangle the DPRK economically and settle the outstanding issues between the DPRK and the U.S. and between the DPRK and Japan in keeping with its intention to stifle the DPRK, says Minju Joson Sunday in a signed commentary.
 Japan put in the amendment such a phrase as "for peace and security" of Japan. Dismissing this as rhetoric to cover up its unjustifiable and criminal intention and mislead the public opinion, the commentary points out that the amendment was aimed to do harm to the other, not to defend itself. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The amendment is a joint product of the ruling and opposition parties of Japan which seek to win popularity and find a way out by making such a shocking practical action as a "measure of applying economic sanctions to the north" in an effort to win in the election of members of Councilors slated for mid-year in the partisan interests and strategy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The commentary brands Japan's passage of the amendment directly hostile to the DPRK as a violation of the DPRK-Japan Pyongyang Declaration and a politically rash act of bedeviling the improvement process of the DPRK-Japan relations.

Special Committee for General Election Formed in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 31 (KCNA) -- The Solidarity for Implementing the South-North Joint Declaration reportedly held the first operation committee meeting for 2004 in Taejon on January 17.
 At the meeting a special committee for general election of the Solidarity for Implementing the South-North Joint Declaration was formed and Director of the South Korean Civil Rights Institute Kim Sung Gyo was elected chairman of the special committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting set arrangement of a political climate for implementing the June 15 joint declaration, expansion and strengthening of progressive mass movement forces and degeneration of the Grand National Party into a minority party as the three-point target of the upcoming general election and raised the establishment of anti-GNP joint front as a basic means of victory in the general election. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting decided to inaugurate headquarters of the general election joint movement for political reform and democracy, headquarters of the movement for the dismantlement of the GNP and veteran group for the promotion of an anti-GNP federation and open an anti-GNP federation website.

Philippine President on Negotiated Settlement of Nuclear Issue
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 31 (KCNA) -- The Philippine government and people maintain the stand that the nuclear issue between the DPRK and the U.S. should be settled through dialogue and negotiations, not through economic blockade against the DPRK, said Philippine President Gloria Macapagal-Arroyo on Jan. 26 when she received credentials from new DPRK Ambassador e.p. to Philippines O Song Chol.
 She said that it is the consistent stand of the Philippine government to further develop the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries in political, economic and trade and other fields. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Korea should be reunified independently and peacefully in the spirit of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration, she noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She hoped that the Korean people would achieve greater success in their endeavors to build a great prosperous powerful socialist nation and reunify the country under the unique Songun revolutionary leadership of Kim Jong Il.

Kim Jong Il's Birthday Celebrated Worldwide
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 31 (KCNA) -- Celebrations have been held in various countries on the occasion of the birthday of leader Kim Jong Il.
 The chairman of the Youth Group for the Study of the Juche Idea of Democratic Congo in a lecture said that Kim Jong Il has brought about a great change in building a great prosperous powerful socialist nation and significantly raised the international prestige of the country with the Songun politics while overcoming all difficulties on the principle of attaching priority to military affairs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chief of the French Group for the Study of the Juche Idea at a seminar noted that Kim Jong Il has performed great feats in all fields including politics, ideology, military affairs and economy by putting everything into practice in line with the idea of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chief of the Group for the Study of the Juche Idea of Poland at a film show said that Kim Jong Il is a great leader of the people, indeed, adding that the future of Korea is rosy as he wisely leads the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The manager of the Homs Electrical Factory in Libya, expressed his envy at the Korean people who are guided by  Kim Jong Il, saying that the Libyan people highly praise and respect the great leader of the Korean people who has the U.S. imperialists under his thumb. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Screened at the film shows were the Korean films "Native House in Mt. Paektu Preserved to Its Former Glory", "They Were Always Together in the Way for the People" and "The Respected Comrade Kim Jong Il Is the Great Thinker and Theoretician". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A letter to Kim Jong Il was adopted at a seminar held in France. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, a joint seminar on his Songun politics was held under the co-sponsorship of the Addis Ababa Group for the Study of the Juche Idea, the Group for the Study of the Juche idea at the Tulubolo Senior Middle School of Ethiopia and a fitness club affiliated to the International Taekwon-Do Federation on Jan. 21.

Seminars on Kim Jong Il's Works Held Abroad
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 31 (KCNA) -- A joint seminar on leader Kim Jong Il's famous work "The Juche Philosophy Is an Original Revolutionary Philosophy" was held in Mexico on Jan. 23.
 The chairman of the Mexican Committee for the Study of Kimilsungism noted that the Juche idea fathered by President Kim Il Sung comprehensively clarified the position and role of man in the world which the preceding theories failed to explain, underscoring the need to learn from the Juche idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the Mexican Institute for the Study of the Juche Idea said that the Juche idea is a great guiding idea in the present times as it is flawless in terms of theory and practice. The DPRK is a great country as it is guided by the Juche idea, he added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, a seminar on Kim Jong Il's famous work "On Preserving the Juche Character and National Character of the Revolution and Construction" was held by the Kim Jong Il Group for the Study of the Juche Idea of the Democratic Congo on Jan. 19.

KCNA Blasts U.S. Arms Buildup
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 31 (KCNA) -- The U.S. was reported to have contemplated spending 425 billion US dollars as a military budget for the year 2004.
 This is all-time high, when recalling that the U.S. annual military expenditure was 342.4 billion US dollars on an average in the period of the Cold War. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. defense spending for 2004 is staggering as it envisages spending at least 1 billion US dollars a day and 43.37 million US dollars per hour except the expenses for its operations in Iraq. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. military expenditure has steadily swollen in recent years and is likely to further increase in the future. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 According to information released by the U.S. Department of Defence, the U.S. defence budget is expected to show an annual increase of about 20 billion US dollars and exceed the level of 500 billion US dollars till 2010 and account for a half of the total military spending in the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This stepped-up arms buildup of the U.S. can not but be a military threat to the whole world as it is aimed to serve its purpose of military intervention, terrorism and war against other countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. policy of unlimited arms buildup is designed to meet its strategic purpose of retaining its military supremacy, stifling those countries which incur its displeasure and seizing the regions of major natural resources and military strategic importance in a bid to establish an American style order of strength in the world and build its unipolar world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. policy of arms buildup serves as a factor of stoking fervour to increase military spending among other countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is well advised to give up its policy of strength based on an adventurous strong-arm theory, going against humankind's desire for global peace and stability.

At least 190 Cases of U.S. Aerial Espionage Committed in January
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 31 (KCNA) -- The U.S. imperialist warmongers have committed more than 190 cases of round-the-clock aerial espionage against the DPRK in January, according to military sources. Involved in them were strategic and tactical reconnaissance planes with various missions based in south Korea and overseas.
 On Jan. 30 "U-2" flew over forefront areas to spy on the depth of the DPRK. And "RC-135", "E-3" and "P-3" also committed espionage against the whole area of the DPRK, its targets in areas along the Military Demarcation Line, its seas and their bottom. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The cases of espionage committed by those planes totalled more than 40 in January. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, ten tactical reconnaissance planes including "RC-7B", "RC-12" and "RF-4C" made shuttle flights over the areas from Tokjok Islet to Phochon and from Phochon to Sokcho Islet to spy on the front and the coastal areas of the DPRK on Jan. 20, nine from Jan. 13 to 15 on a daily average, eight on Jan. 6, 26 and 27 every day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such aerial espionage clearly shows the U.S. imperialists' black-hearted design to mount a sudden preemptive attack on the DPRK anytime as they did to seize Iraq and Afghanistan.
